**Lecture 6, slides 19–21**
- Slide 19: LHC phasor form: Ẽ(z) = a(x̂ + jŷ)e^{−jkz}
- Slide 21: RHC phasor form: Ẽ(z) = a(x̂ − jŷ)e^{−jkz}
- Write aₓx̂ = a_R(x̂ − jŷ) + a_L(x̂ + jŷ) and match real/imaginary components to solve for a_R, a_L

